log.description:
For server administrators only! Gives admin ability to turn on and manage logging feature.

__Public logs__:
`join` New members join;
`left` Members leaving;
`rename` Nickname changes;
`ban` Member bans (requires Audit Log permission);
`kick` Member kicks (requires Audit Log permission).

__Private logs__:
`msg_delete` Message delete;
`msg_image` Message attachments logging;
`msg_update` Message updates.

Some of this features available only if bot have access to server's Audit Log.

top.description:
Showing guild statistics such as:

`channels` `ch` — guild channels activity;
`users` `u` — guild members activity;
`voice` `v` — guild members voice activity.

tracking.description:
Command for managing statistics tracking for users. Allows you to disable or enable tracking.

__Data stored only when tracking enabled:__

+ Your membership in guilds where this bot exist;
+ Amount of time spent by you in voice channels;
+ Amount and size of messages sent by you in all text channels.

__Data which always being stored:__

+ Your user ID;
+ Status of tracking.

